Comment:
****SPOILER ALERT*****
****SPOILER ALERT*****
this movie was frustrating throughout and didn't make a lot of sense in terms of plot. First off, you would think a team that was chosen to go to space to encounter alien life would be at the very least decently smart, but each of them somehow make completely dumb and emotionally driven decisions that ultimately puts them in a shittier situation. Second of all, when Earth sent a capsule to push them into deeper space as a fail-safe move, how is it that only Miranda would know? Why didn't she tell everyone else before hand? Shouldn't there be some sort of procedure so EVERYONE will be aware of what will be happening, instead of having team members guess and possibly make the wrong choice, like Sho did, and blow off the frigging capsule and put the whole shuttle in orbit? You would think that such a HUGE decision like this would be really planned out before hand so no one will do anything stupid. This movie is dumb and every character in it is pretty darn dumb also.

Title: LIFE - Official Trailer #2 (HD)
Comment:
This was, without exaggeration, the WORST space movie in 20 years.  Absolutely idiotic, and even M. Night Shyamalon would think the "plot twist" at the end was absurd given the scenes that happen right up to it.  Granted, you could kind of tell how dumb the movie would be, to an extent, in the trailer, when they are catching the fast-moving space probe with the robot arm.  But it is gratifying to watch some of the bad actors die off at least.  
I know they wanted to be a different kind of space movie, than _The Martian_, etc, and they succeeded -- since those other films were actually good.  They clearly wanted to be an _Alien(s)_ reimagining, but did not succeed.  Not that people will take this movie seriously, but it's also a dumb idea to scare people about the prospects of missions to Mars.
